WEBVTT

00:02.836 --> 00:05.204
Eddie: <i>As a kid, there are</i>
<i>things that terrify you.</i>

00:05.206 --> 00:06.605
Parents,
thank you all for coming.

00:06.607 --> 00:08.273
We know you're very busy,
but we felt

00:08.275 --> 00:10.709
We needed to bring this matter
to your immediate attention.

00:10.711 --> 00:14.780
This man has been seen
in the area

00:14.782 --> 00:16.148
Handing out drugs to children

00:16.150 --> 00:18.050
And telling them
they're stickers.

00:18.052 --> 00:19.351
[ parents murmuring ]

00:19.353 --> 00:21.720
The children then proceed
to lick the stickers

00:21.722 --> 00:23.989
And are then on drugs.
[ murmuring escalates ]

00:23.991 --> 00:26.492
We are working closely
with local authorities,

00:26.494 --> 00:28.560
But we also
wanted to make you aware

00:28.562 --> 00:30.963
So any additional precautions
could be taken.

00:30.965 --> 00:33.999
Yes, you in back.

00:34.001 --> 00:36.268
When do report cards
come out?

00:37.303 --> 00:40.205
<i>In my family,</i>
<i>that's what terrified us.</i>

00:40.207 --> 00:42.307
-- Captions by vitac --

00:42.309 --> 00:43.509
♪ fresh off the boat

00:43.511 --> 00:45.344
♪ I'm gettin' mine
everywhere I go ♪

00:45.346 --> 00:47.513
♪ if you don't know, homey,
now you know ♪

00:47.515 --> 00:48.847
♪ fresh off the boat

00:48.849 --> 00:51.417
♪ homey, you don't know
where I come from ♪

00:51.419 --> 00:52.684
♪ but I know where I'm goin'

00:52.686 --> 00:55.754
♪ I'm fresh off the boat

00:55.756 --> 00:58.524
<i>My mom was singing</i>
<i>at the restaurant</i>

00:58.526 --> 00:59.925
<i>Because my dad thought</i>
<i>it would help business.</i>

00:59.927 --> 01:04.329
♪ a beautiful face
without a name ♪

01:04.331 --> 01:06.899
♪ for so long

01:06.901 --> 01:10.402
♪ a beautiful smile
to hide the pain ♪
well, happy anniversary.

01:10.404 --> 01:12.604
Married 45 years.

01:12.606 --> 01:13.872
I can't imagine it.

01:13.874 --> 01:16.708
♪ did you ever know
that you're my -- ♪

01:16.710 --> 01:18.410
Hey, nancy!

01:18.412 --> 01:19.912
That coupon is expired.

01:19.914 --> 01:21.914
You have to check
the date.

01:21.916 --> 01:24.450
Literally,
I can't imagine it.

01:24.452 --> 01:25.751
How'd she see that?

01:25.753 --> 01:27.853
Jessica:
I see everything.

01:27.855 --> 01:32.958
♪ 'cause you are
the wi-I-I-nd beneath my -- ♪

01:32.960 --> 01:36.428
Okay, just one sprig of parsley
per plate, please.

01:36.430 --> 01:38.964
It is a garnish,
not a salad.

01:38.966 --> 01:39.965
♪ my --

01:39.967 --> 01:41.800
Thank you, thank you.

01:41.802 --> 01:44.603
Uh, the voice of an angel,
the incredible singing lady.

01:44.605 --> 01:45.604
[ applause ]
there we go.

01:45.606 --> 01:47.473
Okay.
[ laughing ]
okay, okay.

01:47.475 --> 01:49.108
She's something else.
Okay.

01:49.110 --> 01:51.577
What are you doing?

01:51.579 --> 01:53.479
The restaurant has been open
almost a month,

01:53.481 --> 01:55.114
And we have been losing money
every day.

01:55.116 --> 01:56.748
We have to tighten up
around here,

01:56.750 --> 01:58.484
Or we will never
turn a profit.

01:58.486 --> 02:00.752
Is that why you clog
half the pepper holes?

02:00.754 --> 02:02.621
Oh, look at that guy,

02:02.623 --> 02:06.058
Shaking away our profits
like he's a pepper monster.

02:06.060 --> 02:07.960
Look, if you're gonna
help with the restaurant,

02:07.962 --> 02:09.061
We need
to get on the same page,

02:09.063 --> 02:10.896
And my page says

02:10.898 --> 02:13.265
The key to success
is to kill them with kindness.

02:13.267 --> 02:14.833
I've always --
shh!
Did you hear that?

02:14.835 --> 02:19.304
Mitch, did you just take
a crouton from the salad bar?

02:20.440 --> 02:22.174
Are you saying
I did not hear a crunch?

02:23.943 --> 02:25.944
You are trying
to dissolve the crouton.

02:25.946 --> 02:27.613
Uh, mitch,
why don't you go see

02:27.615 --> 02:29.681
If any of the servers
need help, okay?

02:29.683 --> 02:30.849
[ chuckles nervously ]

02:33.019 --> 02:35.354
Oh, hell, no.

02:37.123 --> 02:39.358
♪ yeah

02:39.360 --> 02:41.493
Eddie: You waiting
for your report card?

02:41.495 --> 02:43.862
Dave: Yeah, and a birthday card
from my dad.

02:43.864 --> 02:46.031
If it's within three weeks
of your birthday,

02:46.033 --> 02:47.132
Then it still counts.

02:47.134 --> 02:49.668
I've got a forgery kit
in my room.

02:49.670 --> 02:51.770
I'm gonna use it
to change all my c's to b's

02:51.772 --> 02:53.005
Before my mom comes home.

02:53.007 --> 02:54.273
Sweet.
Yeah.

02:54.275 --> 02:57.009
I'm not making the same rookie
mistake I made last year.

02:57.011 --> 02:59.878
Jessica:
Put your gym clothes in the
hamper and take out the trash.

02:59.880 --> 03:02.047
Okay, I will. Love you!

03:02.849 --> 03:05.217
You love me?
What are you hiding?

03:05.219 --> 03:06.351
There's nothing
in my backpack.

03:06.353 --> 03:07.553
Oh, I know.

03:11.691 --> 03:13.025
B-minus!

03:15.461 --> 03:16.962
Is there anything else
for me?

03:16.964 --> 03:18.497
Mailman: Buddy,
we talked about this.

03:18.499 --> 03:21.200
I would lead with the card.
I'm rooting for you.

03:22.869 --> 03:25.204
You ready?
Yeah.

03:29.576 --> 03:31.843
Yes!
Yes!

03:31.845 --> 03:34.012
Mom!
We got
report cards!

03:34.014 --> 03:36.381
Oh. Okay.

03:39.018 --> 03:40.219
What is this?

03:40.221 --> 03:42.020
Our school
doesn't give out grades.

03:42.022 --> 03:44.690
It fosters
unhealthy competition.

03:44.692 --> 03:48.260
Plus/minus rainbow?
One leprechaun?

03:48.262 --> 03:50.262
Two clouds --
that seems bad.

03:50.264 --> 03:51.930
No,
clouds are good.

03:51.932 --> 03:54.099
Clouds are rain.
What are you, a farmer?

03:57.904 --> 03:59.938
[ snoop dogg's "who am I
(what's my name)?" plays ]

03:59.940 --> 04:01.840
♪ the dogg pound's
in the house ♪

04:01.842 --> 04:02.741
♪ the bomb

04:02.743 --> 04:04.943
♪ ee-yi-yi, yi-yi-yi

04:04.945 --> 04:08.413
♪ the dogg pound's
in the house ♪

04:08.415 --> 04:12.451
♪ snoop doggy dogg

04:12.453 --> 04:13.919
♪ the bomb

04:13.921 --> 04:14.886
♪ snoop doggy --
[ button clicks, music stops ]

04:14.888 --> 04:16.755
[ grandma speaks chinese ]

04:16.757 --> 04:18.690
Domino!
Straight a's, moms!

04:18.692 --> 04:20.392
The one good thing
about moving here

04:20.394 --> 04:22.894
Is I have no friends
and no distractions.

04:22.896 --> 04:24.062
That's why I got a --

04:24.064 --> 04:26.031
Grandma,
what does fonzie say?

04:26.033 --> 04:28.867
"a"!
[ hisses ]

04:33.373 --> 04:35.140
School is too easy.

04:35.142 --> 04:37.109
Eddie: Just when you think
you've won the game,

04:37.111 --> 04:38.944
This trick
done changed the rules.

04:38.946 --> 04:40.445
Eddie, don't call your mother
a trick.

04:40.447 --> 04:42.914
You need to make school
more challenging,

04:42.916 --> 04:44.983
Or else my son
will fall behind.

04:44.985 --> 04:46.652
I'm sorry.
There's not much I can do

04:46.654 --> 04:48.086
About
a straight-"a" student.

04:48.088 --> 04:49.054
Well,
is there extra school?

04:49.056 --> 04:51.323
Where is
the closest clc?

04:51.325 --> 04:53.959
Oh, no.

04:53.961 --> 04:55.260
What's clc?

04:55.262 --> 04:59.131
<i>Chinese learning center --</i>
<i>an after-school program</i>

04:59.133 --> 05:03.969
<i>For reading, math, science,</i>
<i>and violin.</i>

05:03.971 --> 05:07.839
[ violin playing ]

05:07.841 --> 05:09.941
<i>Look at them, the innocence.</i>

05:09.943 --> 05:12.077
<i>I couldn't hear them</i>
<i>through the reinforced glass,</i>

05:12.079 --> 05:15.647
<i>But I imagined</i>
<i>it was the sound of childhood.</i>

05:15.649 --> 05:18.283
<i>Enjoy your stick,</i>
<i>white friends.</i>

05:18.285 --> 05:21.086
I'm sorry. We don't have
a chinese learning center here.

05:21.088 --> 05:22.421
Yes!

05:22.423 --> 05:24.923
But we do have
an after-school program

05:24.925 --> 05:26.158
Called animal encounters

05:26.160 --> 05:27.693
Where we bring in
farm animals

05:27.695 --> 05:29.361
For the children
to play with.

05:29.363 --> 05:32.698
In fact, I have a baby chick
in my lap right now.

05:34.200 --> 05:36.501
[ chick chirping ]

05:36.503 --> 05:39.671
Please put your lap chicken
away.

05:40.807 --> 05:43.108
Jessica: I don't understand
these people.

05:43.110 --> 05:46.345
It's like success
is not important to them.

05:46.347 --> 05:49.181
To spencer
and his four c's.

05:49.183 --> 05:50.282
[ glasses clink ]

05:50.284 --> 05:51.316
Unh-unh!

05:51.318 --> 05:53.852
Nancy,
no wasting napkins.

05:53.854 --> 05:56.688
Uh, but the lady at table six
asked for it.

05:56.690 --> 05:58.123
She ordered a salad.

05:58.125 --> 05:59.224
She does not
need an extra napkin.

05:59.226 --> 06:00.292
[ sighs ]

06:02.161 --> 06:03.195
My hands are tied.

06:04.530 --> 06:07.199
Jessica,
we talked about this.

06:07.201 --> 06:09.000
It's a slippery slope.

06:09.002 --> 06:10.802
First,
an employee pops a crouton.

06:10.804 --> 06:13.138
Next thing you know,
they are wheeling ovens
out of the kitchen.

06:13.140 --> 06:15.006
Same with the customer.

06:15.008 --> 06:16.541
First,
they get extra napkin.

06:16.543 --> 06:18.677
Next thing you know,
they run out on the bill.

06:18.679 --> 06:20.212
Same with the boys.

06:20.214 --> 06:22.180
First, they have baby chickens
in their lap.

06:22.182 --> 06:24.649
Next thing you know,
they are homeless!

06:26.986 --> 06:31.022
You know, just because
they don't offer clc here

06:31.024 --> 06:33.759
Doesn't mean <i>you</i> can't
provide it for the boys.

06:33.761 --> 06:35.060
Well,
I'm not a teacher.

06:35.062 --> 06:37.896
No,
but you are very smart.

06:37.898 --> 06:39.064
I mean,
have you ever met

06:39.066 --> 06:40.832
A "wheel of fortune" puzzle
you couldn't figure out?

06:40.834 --> 06:42.734
I always guess them.
Mm-hmm.

06:42.736 --> 06:45.504
I mean, you're way smarter than
the teachers they had at clc.

06:45.506 --> 06:47.239
Some of them
were not impressive.

06:47.241 --> 06:48.240
Mnh-mnh.

06:48.242 --> 06:49.841
Oh, never mind.

06:49.843 --> 06:51.042
You can't teach the boys
clc.

06:51.044 --> 06:53.078
I mean, what would I do
at the restaurant?

06:53.080 --> 06:54.246
You are so valuable
here.

06:54.248 --> 06:56.181
I really am.
Yeah.

06:56.183 --> 06:59.918
But we do have a crisis
on our hands.

06:59.920 --> 07:02.154
Our boys
did get straight a's.

07:09.595 --> 07:10.695
Dave:
Oh, hey, man.

07:10.697 --> 07:12.297
Look what my mom got me
for my straight c's.

07:12.299 --> 07:13.432
You want to play?

07:13.434 --> 07:15.500
Does the yellow man
like dumplings?

07:16.636 --> 07:17.636
We do, we do.
Sorry.

07:17.638 --> 07:18.970
I put you
in an awkward spot.

07:18.972 --> 07:20.739
Let me go get
my breakaway pants

07:20.741 --> 07:23.008
So I can rip them off.

07:25.111 --> 07:26.111
[ grunts ]

07:26.113 --> 07:27.546
We're doing clc.

07:27.548 --> 07:29.080
But there aren't any
in orlando.

07:29.082 --> 07:31.516
There is now --
homeschool clc.

07:32.452 --> 07:34.286
I will be your teacher.

07:44.330 --> 07:45.564
Time.

07:47.767 --> 07:49.835
[ basketball dribbling ]

07:53.406 --> 07:55.507
Eddie, focus!

07:55.509 --> 07:56.608
[ sighs ]

07:56.610 --> 07:58.477
Okay, I need
to start making dinner.

07:58.479 --> 08:02.514
Evan, you make sure
that everyone does their clc.

08:02.516 --> 08:04.783
Okay,
teacher mommy.

08:04.785 --> 08:06.084
[ pen clatters ]
you're loving this.

08:06.086 --> 08:08.353
Teacher's pet
<i>and</i> mama's boy.

08:08.355 --> 08:10.288
I'm writing you up.

08:10.290 --> 08:12.357
"student -- eddie huang.

08:12.359 --> 08:14.159
Infraction -- not nice."

08:14.161 --> 08:15.660
[ pen slams ]

08:15.662 --> 08:17.596
[ pen clicks ]

08:17.598 --> 08:20.365
"student -- eddie huang."

08:20.367 --> 08:21.933
This sucks, right,
emery?

08:21.935 --> 08:23.435
You play
the cards you're dealt.

08:23.437 --> 08:24.936
Choose life, you know?

08:26.772 --> 08:28.540
[ door slams ]

08:30.643 --> 08:33.111
Aw, man, a trampoline?

08:33.113 --> 08:36.081
And he's using it
inappropriately?

08:37.116 --> 08:39.017
Oh!

08:39.019 --> 08:42.187
I never get
to have that much fun.

08:45.224 --> 08:47.726
Oh, uh, I'm sorry.
I was --

08:47.728 --> 08:50.729
No, no, it's okay.
You can have a crouton.

08:50.731 --> 08:52.531
Is this a trick?

08:52.533 --> 08:53.698
Is she here?
Is she watching us?

08:53.700 --> 08:55.834
Are you tricking me?
No, no.
It's not a trick.

08:55.836 --> 08:57.202
It's a trick.
There's cameras, right?

08:57.204 --> 08:58.537
Stop, stop.
Where is she?

08:58.539 --> 08:59.704
Look at me.

08:59.706 --> 09:02.140
Mitch, when you're
at cattleman's ranch,

09:02.142 --> 09:03.675
I want you to feel like

09:03.677 --> 09:06.845
You're being hugged by a
matronly woman with chubby arms.

09:06.847 --> 09:08.880
That's
how I want to feel.

09:08.882 --> 09:10.715
[ chuckles ]
see, I believe

09:10.717 --> 09:13.051
That happy employees
are good employees

09:13.053 --> 09:15.020
And good employees
are good for business.

09:15.022 --> 09:16.821
So how about this?

09:16.823 --> 09:20.592
You and I, we're gonna
have a crouton together, okay?

09:20.594 --> 09:21.760
R-really?

09:21.762 --> 09:23.895
So I'm gonna take one,
and you're gonna take one.

09:23.897 --> 09:25.330
Cheers.
Cheers.

09:25.332 --> 09:26.498
Ding!
Cheers.

09:26.500 --> 09:29.067
[ crunching ]

09:29.069 --> 09:30.869
They're pretty good.

09:30.871 --> 09:32.604
Very good. [ laughs ]

09:32.606 --> 09:36.308
I know that you aren't
a matronly woman, but...

09:37.710 --> 09:38.743
Bring it.

09:38.745 --> 09:40.078
All right.
Bring it, bring it.

09:40.080 --> 09:42.280
[ both chuckling ]

09:42.282 --> 09:44.916
All right.
[ laughs ]

09:44.918 --> 09:46.451
Okay, we're good.
Okay.

09:46.453 --> 09:47.719
Okay.
Just one more. Nice.
Okay.

09:47.721 --> 09:50.188
You're a good man,
you know?
Thank you.

09:50.190 --> 09:52.757
Okay.
You're a really good man.
Thank you.

09:52.759 --> 09:54.092
Okay.
Oh, that was fun.

09:54.094 --> 09:56.461
We should do that
all the time.
No.

09:57.697 --> 09:59.097
[ door opens ]

09:59.099 --> 10:02.133
Whoo! Rough day
at the ranch.

10:02.135 --> 10:04.603
Is nancy messing up
the iced teas again?

10:04.605 --> 10:08.406
I told her it is 4 cups of water
to 1 tea bag.

10:08.408 --> 10:10.942
It is so hard
to not have you there.

10:10.944 --> 10:13.612
But this is best
for the boys.

10:13.614 --> 10:15.780
Our sacrifice
will be worth it.

10:15.782 --> 10:17.015
[ chuckles lightly ]

10:17.883 --> 10:20.652
Mom, eddie's refusing
to use the bathroom pass.

10:20.654 --> 10:23.955
I'm not trying to use a pass
to whiz in my own house.

10:23.957 --> 10:26.558
Dinner's almost ready.
You finish your clc?

10:26.560 --> 10:27.826
You know I didn't.

10:27.828 --> 10:30.595
Dinner <i>after</i> clc.

10:30.597 --> 10:31.763
[ sighs ]

10:31.765 --> 10:34.666
Dad, mom is crazy.

10:34.668 --> 10:37.736
Can't you talk some sense
into her?

10:37.738 --> 10:39.904
Uh, well, you know, it's, uh,
tough for all of us.

10:39.906 --> 10:41.439
I'm dying without her
at the restaurant.

10:41.441 --> 10:44.275
Nobody's having a good time.
Love you!

10:44.277 --> 10:46.611
<i>Love you?</i>
<i>My dad never said that.</i>

10:46.613 --> 10:48.913
<i>My family loved each other.</i>
<i>We just didn't say it.</i>

10:48.915 --> 10:51.016
<i>We showed our love through</i>
<i>criticism and micromanagement,</i>

10:51.018 --> 10:53.351
<i>So if you said "love you,"</i>

10:53.353 --> 10:55.687
<i>You were probably</i>
<i>hiding something.</i>

10:55.689 --> 10:57.856
Louis:
[ laughing ] okay.

10:57.858 --> 10:59.591
Here you are.
Oh, I'm okay.

10:59.593 --> 11:01.159
I don't need any extra napkins.
Thank you.

11:01.161 --> 11:03.128
I beg to differ.

11:03.130 --> 11:04.295
Boop!

11:04.297 --> 11:06.898
[ both laugh ]

11:10.369 --> 11:12.604
Nancy: Hey,
we have a jukebox?

11:12.606 --> 11:13.872
I guess so.

11:13.874 --> 11:15.974
Hey, mitch,
go ahead and plug her in.

11:15.976 --> 11:17.108
Really?

11:17.110 --> 11:20.178
Happy employees
equal happy customers.

11:20.180 --> 11:21.880
[ calypso music plays ]

11:21.882 --> 11:25.850
It's like we've been
whisked away to trinidad.

11:25.852 --> 11:27.852
[ laughter ]

11:34.960 --> 11:37.228
Aw, hell, no!

11:41.000 --> 11:42.167
♪ ee-yi-yi, yi-yi-yi

11:42.169 --> 11:44.035
♪ the dogg pound's
in the house ♪

11:44.037 --> 11:46.571
I'm too excited
to pimp-walk.

11:46.573 --> 11:50.208
[ speaks chinese ]

11:50.210 --> 11:51.810
Dad doesn't want you
at the restaurant.

11:51.812 --> 11:53.044
What?
That's not true.

11:53.046 --> 11:55.747
Your father
is struggling without me,

11:55.749 --> 11:58.516
But he is making a sacrifice
for your education.

11:58.518 --> 12:00.485
Ask him yourself.

12:00.487 --> 12:02.420
Of course
I want you here.

12:02.422 --> 12:03.922
It is awful without you.

12:03.924 --> 12:06.024
I <i>am</i> very good.

12:06.026 --> 12:07.759
Eddie's
just making up excuses,

12:07.761 --> 12:09.060
Probably to get out of clc.

12:09.062 --> 12:10.929
I will double
his workload.

12:10.931 --> 12:13.531
Oh, no. Got to run.
I see mitch eyeing the croutons.

12:13.533 --> 12:14.666
Love you!

12:14.668 --> 12:16.167
[ receiver clicks, dial tone ]

12:16.169 --> 12:17.902
Aw, hell, no!

12:17.904 --> 12:19.838
[ calypso music plays ]

12:19.840 --> 12:21.873
[ laughs ]
everybody having a good time?

12:21.875 --> 12:23.041
[ laughter ]

12:23.043 --> 12:27.879
If this jukebox
uses 50 kilowatts of power

12:27.881 --> 12:30.048
At 11 cents per kilowatt

12:30.050 --> 12:32.684
And a 3-minute song
costs 25 cents,

12:32.686 --> 12:34.886
How much money do we lose
per song?

12:34.888 --> 12:35.954
2 1/2 cents!
2 1/2 --

12:35.956 --> 12:37.555
Aw, man!

12:37.557 --> 12:40.925
And this is why
I never plug in the jukebox.

12:40.927 --> 12:44.295
Boys, welcome
to your new clc classroom.

12:44.297 --> 12:45.530
[ to the tune of "escape"
(the piña colada song)" ]

12:45.532 --> 12:47.732
♪ if you like
mini garlic croutons ♪

12:47.734 --> 12:49.467
♪ a great snack on the...

12:49.469 --> 12:51.035
♪ go

12:51.037 --> 12:52.737
Hi.

12:52.739 --> 12:54.305
Uh, may I get you
some waters

12:54.307 --> 12:56.541
Or perhaps
a blooming onion?

13:04.416 --> 13:06.151
Jessica, what brings you
to cattleman's ranch?

13:06.153 --> 13:09.487
I realize -- why not
have the boys do clc here?

13:09.489 --> 13:12.557
That way, I can also help you
at the restaurant.

13:12.559 --> 13:14.826
Unless
you don't want me here.

13:14.828 --> 13:17.061
Oh, no.
Of course I want you here.

13:17.063 --> 13:19.464
Good!
Boys, clc, this booth.

13:20.766 --> 13:24.903
If mitch steals
two croutons per hour

13:24.905 --> 13:27.338
And a 3-pound box costs $5,

13:27.340 --> 13:29.974
How many days
till we are on the street?

13:29.976 --> 13:31.409
How many croutons
per box?

13:31.411 --> 13:33.111
What are we paying
in rent?

13:33.113 --> 13:35.346
How can I solve for "x"
when I don't know "z"?

13:35.348 --> 13:36.581
[ coughs ] nerd.
[ pen clicks ]

13:36.583 --> 13:39.350
"student -- eddie huang.

13:39.352 --> 13:42.187
Infraction -- slander."

13:42.189 --> 13:43.588
He's tough,
but he's fair.

13:43.590 --> 13:47.125
Nancy, what did I tell you
about extra napkins?

13:47.127 --> 13:49.360
Also,
why are we out of tea bags?

13:49.362 --> 13:50.595
I don't want you here.

13:50.597 --> 13:51.796
I knew it,

13:51.798 --> 13:54.666
As soon as you expressed
emotions with words.

13:54.668 --> 13:56.434
Why do you micromanage
everything?

13:56.436 --> 13:59.771
Why am I the only one who cares
that we are losing money?

13:59.773 --> 14:01.306
I'm just looking out
for our family.

14:01.308 --> 14:03.374
So am I, but I'm doing it
in a nicer way.

14:03.376 --> 14:05.777
You should treat people
the way you want to be treated.

14:05.779 --> 14:08.980
You think people are inherently
good, but they are not.

14:08.982 --> 14:10.481
Woman: I'm sorry.

14:10.483 --> 14:11.816
Could I just get my check,
please?

14:11.818 --> 14:13.184
No, <i>I'm</i> sorry.

14:13.186 --> 14:14.686
My son got straight a's,
and I told my wife I love her.

14:14.688 --> 14:15.720
Please bear with us.

14:15.722 --> 14:17.322
We're going through
a rough patch.

14:17.324 --> 14:18.790
Look at that table.
Look at that table.

14:18.792 --> 14:20.792
They are
about to dine and dash.

14:20.794 --> 14:23.561
They've ordered the most
expensive items on the menu.

14:23.563 --> 14:25.530
They've been there a long time,
and they haven't paid.

14:25.532 --> 14:28.633
[ air hissing ]
and that one guy is pumping up
his sneaker.

14:28.635 --> 14:30.535
I'll take care of this.

14:30.537 --> 14:32.570
How? By killing them
with kindness,

14:32.572 --> 14:35.039
Showering them
with napkins?

14:35.041 --> 14:37.375
No, you make them pay,
then you kick them out.

14:37.377 --> 14:39.377
I will handle this
my way.

14:41.680 --> 14:42.881
Hello.

14:42.883 --> 14:44.515
We're not
done eating yet.

14:44.517 --> 14:46.184
I know, I know.
Look...

14:46.186 --> 14:48.987
I know
what you guys are doing here.

14:48.989 --> 14:50.321
You're gonna dine and dash

14:50.323 --> 14:52.357
Because you think it's fun
and nobody gets hurt.

14:52.359 --> 14:55.193
But this is
a family business.

14:55.195 --> 14:57.228
It's not run
by some big corporation.

14:57.230 --> 14:58.897
I thought
this was a golden corral.

14:58.899 --> 15:01.332
It's a totally different
restaurant!

15:01.334 --> 15:02.734
The bears
aren't even the same color.

15:02.736 --> 15:05.203
Look, if you guys run out
on this check,

15:05.205 --> 15:07.438
It's gonna
come out of <i>our</i> pocket --

15:07.440 --> 15:10.108
Me, my wife,
and my three boys.

15:10.110 --> 15:11.843
You guys were really going
for a little girl, huh?

15:11.845 --> 15:13.778
Don't get me started.
We were gonna name her emily.

15:13.780 --> 15:15.213
That's sweet.
Aww.

15:15.215 --> 15:16.281
Yeah.

15:16.283 --> 15:19.550
Look, the point is,
we're not rich.

15:19.552 --> 15:22.553
In fact, we're struggling
just to break even.

15:22.555 --> 15:25.556
So if you guys order
more than you can pay for,

15:25.558 --> 15:27.358
We can work something out.

15:29.261 --> 15:30.461
Yeah, okay.
I -- we're sorry.

15:30.463 --> 15:31.796
We're just being stupid.

15:31.798 --> 15:34.399
And we can cover it.
I got my dad's credit card.

15:34.401 --> 15:37.435
Thanks, guys.
I appreciate it. [ chuckles ]

15:42.107 --> 15:43.942
I took care of it.

15:43.944 --> 15:46.477
I talked to them the way that
I would want to be talked to,

15:46.479 --> 15:47.712
And they got it.

15:47.714 --> 15:48.980
People are good.

15:48.982 --> 15:52.784
Are you sure about that?

16:01.560 --> 16:04.729
I'll be in my office.

16:06.598 --> 16:08.466
Mitch:
Excuse me, mrs. Huang?

16:08.468 --> 16:09.767
Um,
we were just talking,

16:09.769 --> 16:11.836
And we'd like
to cover their check.

16:11.838 --> 16:13.504
What?

16:13.506 --> 16:14.672
The table that ran out --

16:14.674 --> 16:16.674
We want to chip in
and pay their bill.

16:16.676 --> 16:18.576
Yeah, louis would do it
for us.

16:18.578 --> 16:20.678
I mean,
he's a great boss.

16:22.247 --> 16:24.816
Mom, eddie dined and dashed
on clc.

16:24.818 --> 16:28.353
But don't worry.
I wrote him another infraction.

16:28.355 --> 16:32.190
[ cypress hill's
"insane in the membrane" plays ]

16:32.192 --> 16:34.625
[ horn honks ]

16:34.627 --> 16:36.160
Oh, crap!

16:36.162 --> 16:37.895
I will get to you later!

16:42.434 --> 16:44.869
"run out on this bill,
it comes out of our pocket."
[ laughs ]

16:44.871 --> 16:46.537
[ tires screech, both grunt ]

16:46.539 --> 16:47.672
Hey.

16:56.548 --> 16:58.549
[ grunts ]

16:58.551 --> 17:00.451
Oh!

17:00.453 --> 17:01.652
Emery,
go get that onion.

17:01.654 --> 17:03.788
I'm going to cook dinner with it
tonight.

17:03.790 --> 17:06.691
Time me.

17:08.060 --> 17:09.627
You hit us with your car.

17:09.629 --> 17:11.696
You hit my car
with your bodies.

17:11.698 --> 17:13.865
My husband is a good man.

17:13.867 --> 17:15.800
He believes
in the good of people.

17:15.802 --> 17:17.068
I don't.

17:17.070 --> 17:19.804
But all his employees respect
and admire him,

17:19.806 --> 17:21.472
Which, uh,
makes you start to wonder.

17:21.474 --> 17:22.507
My body feels cold.

17:22.509 --> 17:24.008
I-I-it's shutting down.

17:24.010 --> 17:25.710
My point is,

17:25.712 --> 17:28.913
I don't want my husband
to lose his faith in people.

17:28.915 --> 17:30.882
Okay, okay.
W-we'll pay our check.

17:30.884 --> 17:33.751
You are going to do
a lot more than that.

17:33.753 --> 17:37.321
Emery: I don't know why,
but it's warm!

17:37.323 --> 17:39.524
After we left,
we thought about what you said,

17:39.526 --> 17:40.658
And we realized
you were right.

17:40.660 --> 17:42.160
Yeah, what we did
was wrong.

17:42.162 --> 17:44.796
Really?
Yes.

17:45.764 --> 17:48.232
You were right
to see the good in us.

17:50.736 --> 17:52.403
Did you have something to do
with this?

17:52.405 --> 17:53.871
What? Me?

17:53.873 --> 17:55.006
No.

17:55.008 --> 17:57.708
Okay, well, I'm gonna go
make dinner now --

17:57.710 --> 17:59.544
Sliced beef with peppers
and onions,

17:59.546 --> 18:02.013
Maybe some rice, also.

18:02.015 --> 18:03.514
Love you!

18:03.516 --> 18:07.785
[ ice cube's
"it was a good day" plays ]

18:20.799 --> 18:22.733
I missed all the fun.

18:22.735 --> 18:24.902
Hmm.

18:24.904 --> 18:26.637
Well, you know,

18:26.639 --> 18:28.739
Most moms don't care enough
about their kids

18:28.741 --> 18:30.374
To tutor them
for two hours a day.

18:30.376 --> 18:31.642
It was three hours.

18:31.644 --> 18:33.377
Three hours?!

18:33.379 --> 18:35.713
My god, I [scoffs]

18:35.715 --> 18:36.747
[ sighs ]

18:36.749 --> 18:40.685
Look, I'm not gonna lie.
Your mom is tough.

18:41.653 --> 18:44.288
And she's never gonna let up
on you or any of us,

18:44.290 --> 18:46.891
But it's because
she cares.

18:48.093 --> 18:49.727
Yeah.

18:49.729 --> 18:52.830
♪ I got to go
'cause I got me a drop-top ♪

18:52.832 --> 18:54.232
♪ and if I hit the switch

18:54.234 --> 18:56.501
♪ I can make the ass drop

18:56.503 --> 18:58.669
♪ had to stop at a red light

18:58.671 --> 19:00.838
You think
you can beat your old man?

19:00.840 --> 19:02.507
Dad, you serve people
all day.

19:02.509 --> 19:03.741
You ready to get served?

19:03.743 --> 19:05.743
[ laughs ]
wait,
I almost forgot.

19:06.678 --> 19:08.479
That felt good.

19:08.481 --> 19:10.815
♪ called up the homies,
and I'm asking y'all ♪

19:10.817 --> 19:13.918
♪ which park
are y'all playing basketball? ♪

19:13.920 --> 19:15.820
♪ get me on the court
and I'm trouble ♪
aw!
Ooh, close.

19:15.822 --> 19:18.656
Ooh! Nice, nice!

19:18.658 --> 19:19.690
Close.

19:19.692 --> 19:22.160
♪ freaking brothers
every way like m.J. ♪

19:22.162 --> 19:24.195
♪ I can't believe
today was a good day ♪

19:24.197 --> 19:25.363
Mom said we can play.

19:25.365 --> 19:26.631
Nobody block my shots.

19:26.633 --> 19:29.033
Louis:
Come on, come on.

19:29.035 --> 19:30.868
♪ today was a good day

19:34.873 --> 19:36.174
Oh, hey.

19:36.176 --> 19:38.142
♪ I was glad
everything had worked out ♪

19:38.144 --> 19:39.844
Is that your dad?
Yeah.

19:39.846 --> 19:42.713
♪ dropped the one off
and then chirped out ♪
seems like a cool guy.

19:42.715 --> 19:44.115
Ooh! All day!

19:44.117 --> 19:45.950
♪ today was like
one of those fly dreams ♪
you want to play?

19:45.952 --> 19:48.719
Well, I was just gonna
flip through sports games on tv

19:48.721 --> 19:51.856
And look for my dad in the
crowds, but I guess I can wait.

19:51.858 --> 19:52.790
Yeah, come on.

19:52.792 --> 19:55.193
♪ I got to say
it was a good day ♪

19:55.195 --> 19:57.895
That's how it was in my family.

19:57.897 --> 19:59.664
<i>We didn't do sappy</i>
<i>"I love yous."</i>

19:59.666 --> 20:00.831
<i>We didn't have to.</i>

20:00.833 --> 20:03.334
<i>We just showed it.</i>

20:03.336 --> 20:07.138
Looks like we'll be going
for academic scholarships.

20:11.410 --> 20:13.377
And then an alligator sticker
plus a cloud sticker

20:13.379 --> 20:15.813
Equals an alligator
with sunglasses sticker.

20:15.815 --> 20:16.981
All right, so --

20:16.983 --> 20:19.183
Unless the cloud sticker
is a rain cloud,

20:19.185 --> 20:22.253
In which case it reverts
back to a bear in a hat.

20:22.255 --> 20:24.088
Oh, right. So --

20:24.090 --> 20:25.990
Unless the bear's hat
is black,

20:25.992 --> 20:28.092
Which indicates
a very high level of effort.

20:28.094 --> 20:28.926
So...

20:28.928 --> 20:30.061
Which is then rewarded

20:30.063 --> 20:32.263
By a plus/minus
participatory rainbow,

20:32.265 --> 20:35.499
Of which there are
three intensity hues.

20:35.501 --> 20:38.102
[ speaks chinese ]

20:39.738 --> 20:41.072
What'd your mom say?

20:41.074 --> 20:43.574
She gave you
an alligator with sunglasses.

20:43.576 --> 20:46.444
And to you.
